  "question": "A60-year-old woman with mild hypertension is admitted for elective hysterectomy. On preoperative evaluation, she is found to have osteoarthritis; over the previous 6 months, she had noted watery diarrhea that was becoming progressively worse. The serum potassium is 3 mEq/L. Which is the most likely cause of hypokalemia?",
