  "answer": "B) Villous adenoma of colon can result in watery diarrhea and hypokalemia. Massive tissue injury producing myoglobinemia is associated with significant release of intracellular potassium. Massive blood transfusion results in release of large amounts of potassium. The ability to excrete potassium is impaired in high-output renal failure. Spironolactone is a potassium-sparing diuretic.",
