  "answer": "E) In the anesthetized patient, the classic signs of transfusion reaction are masked. The sudden unexplained onset of bleeding and hypoten-sion should include transfusion reaction in the differential diagnosis. In the conscious patient, chills, fever, pain in the lumbar region, a tight sensation over the chest, flushing of the face, and dark-colored urine may be evident.",
  "chapter": "General Surgery",
