  "answer": "D) Thrombocytopenia is a common complica-tion of heparin therapy. The most common form, type I (seen in up to 30% of patients), is a milder form that occurs after 2–3 days of heparin therapy.The platelet count remains over 50,000/mm3 and has no clinical significance. Type II, seen in 1–2%, usually occurs 7–10 days after heparin treatment. It is immune mediated and can be caused by heparin therapy in any form, in any dose, including heparin flushes and heparin-bonded intravenous catheters. Treat-ment consists of immediate cessation of heparin administration in any form.",
