  "question": "A 25-year-old man sustained laceration of the liver and rupture of the spleen in an automo-bile accident. He was hypotensive for more than 1 hour and received 10 L of crystalloids and 10 U of blood. On the second postoperative day, he is intubated, his HR is 120 bpm, his BP is 110/60 mm Hg, his urine output is 40 mL/h, and his CVP is 13 cm H O. His ABGs on 70% oxygen reveal a pH of 7.42, a PO of 58 mm Hg, and a PCO of 35 mm Hg. What is the most appropriate management?",
