  "answer": "B) Disseminated intravascular coagulation is characterized by diffuse intravascular coagu-lation, thrombosis, and fibrinolysis. It results in thrombocytopenia, hypofibrinogenemia, pro-longation of PT and PTT, and increased con-centration of fibrin degradation products in plasma. Sepsis is a major factor that can trigger DIC.",
  "chapter": "General Surgery",
