  "answer": "C) Galactorrhea is fairly common up to old age. The discharge may vary in color from brown to milky. Hormonal causes are associ-ated with elevated prolactin levels or with pitu-itary or thyroid disorders. Tranquilizers have also been implicated. Simple abscesses do not cause galactorrhea.",
  "chapter": "General Surgery",
