  "question": "A28-year-old female figure skater presents sev-eral weeks after having sustained an injury to her left breast. She has a painful mass in the upper outer quadrant. Skin retraction is noticed, and a hard mass, 3–4 cm in diameter, can easily be palpated. What is the most likely diagnosis?",
