  "answer": "D) Follow-up after breast cancer treatment is very variable. There is no consensus and no follow-up test has shown a survival advantage. Routine 3–6 month clinical examinations and yearly mammography should always be per-formed. The use of tumor markers such as a CA15-3 has not shown any proven significant value and may lead to unnecessary worry.",
  "chapter": "General Surgery",
