  "id": 130146,
  "question": "An 85-year-old ventilator-dependent male was endotracheally intubated 10 days ago. He remains unresponsive and is not a candidate for early extubation. The intensive care unit (ICU) attending elects to perform tracheotomy at the bedside. During the procedure, copious dark blood is encountered. This is most likely due to transection of which of the following:",
