  "question": "While lecturing to her advanced psychology students, a 55-year-old college professor com-plains of acute onset strained, raspy fluctuat-ing voice, forcing her to discontinue her lecture and seek urgent ear, nose, and throat (ENT) evaluation. Which diagnosis is most likely:",
