  "question": "A3-year-old child presented to the emergency room with thin, gray pus dripping from her left nostril. Her foster mother stated that the child “always had a cold” for as long as she knew her during the past year. Prior treatment with oral antibiotics failed to relieve the symp-toms. What was the most likely source of the chronic discharge?",
