  "answer": "E) Papillary cystadenoma lymphomatosum is also called Warthin’s tumor. It occurs mainly in men. The epithelial component is interspersed with lymphoid tissue that shows germinal cen-ters. The most common tumor of the parotid gland is a pleomorphic adenoma, with papil-lary cystadenoma (although much less fre-quent) as the second most common tumor. Mikulicz’s disease involves chronic inflamma-tion and swelling of the salivary glands, which is benign and usually painless.",
