  "question": "An asymptomatic 56-year-old man is found on routine chest x-ray to have a 2-cm nodule-cen-tral tumor in the upper lobe of the right lung. The lesion is not calcified. No previous x-rays exist. What is the most appropriate initial step toward making a diagnosis?",
