  "question": "A 42-year-old man known to have Marfan’s syndrome is admitted to the emergency depart-ment with severe chest pain radiating to the back. His blood pressure is 190/130 mm Hg. An electrocardiogram (ECG) shows no evidence of myocardial infarction. Atype I (ascending aorta) dissecting aneurysm is detected on angiogra-phy. What should he undergo?",
