  "question": "A 4-year-old girl is diagnosed with bilateral otitis media and is treated for 10 days with an oral broad-spectrum antibiotic. The patient completes the full course of antibiotics and returns for regular follow-up visits. In most children, the appearance of the tympanic membrane returns to normal following a single antibiotic regimen for an episode of otitis media within what period?",
