  "answer": "B) 109. (B) Definitive treatment of hyperparathyroidism is parathyroidectomy. When serum calcium is above 14 mgm/dL the patient is in hypercalcemic crisis. Immediate treatment of this condition requires hydration with normal saline and use of diuretics to bring down the serum calcium level. A positive parathyroid scan will help to locate an adenoma of the parathyroid preoperatively.",
