  "question": "During a routine examination of a 30-year-old female actuary seeking life insurance, she is found to have a ventricular septal defect (VSD). She undergoes subsequent studies including ECG, chest x-ray, echocardiography, and Doppler ultrasound. What is the major determinant of operability in VSD?",
