  "question": "At birth, the 6 weeks premature infant is noted to have progressive dyspnea. There is a continuous murmur in the pulmonic area (second left intercostal space), and cyanosis is absent. ECG findings are normal. An x-ray of the heart shows cardiomegaly, and the pulse is bounding. Patent ductus arteriosus (PDA) is diagnosed. What does treatment include?",
