  "question": "A 23-year-old ballet dancer is concerned about the recent sudden death of a young famous Russian dancer on a New York stage. The patient seeks advice about his own risk for developing cardiac disease. His father died suddenly from ischemic heart disease at the age of 40. What is the most important risk factor that would further indicate the possibility of coronary artery heart disease?",
