  "id": 130287,
  "question": "Following a car accident, a 52-year-old lawyer complains of pain in the left abdomen and back. After arrival of the EMS team, her pulse rate is 84 bpm, but of small volume. She states that she has some cardiac condition but is uncertain of its nature. Which is the most likely cause of the small pulse volume?",
