  "answer": "E) Duodenal ulcer is best diagnosed by upper endoscopy and biopsy. Findings of gastritis and the presence of H.pylori are indications to prescribe appropriate therapy. This typically includes a PPI and two antibiotics (one regimen includes amoxicillin and clarithromycin). Although the urea breath test is the most sen-sitive and specific test used to detect H. pylori, it is not readily available in all settings.",
