  "question": "Afrail elderly patient is found to have an ante-rior perforation of a duodenal ulcer. He has a recent history of nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID) use and no previous history of peptic ulcer disease. A large amount of bilious fluid is found in the abdomen. What should be the next step?",
