  "answer": "E) There is a varying degree of impairment in carbohydrate, fat, protein, and mineral absorp-tion after gastrectomy. These changes are most severe after a subtotal gastrectomy and gastro-jejunostomy (Billroth II) (Fig. 5–7), in most patients these changes are mild. An acid envi-ronment is necessary to release ferric ion from food and make it available for absorption in the small intestine.",
  "chapter": "General Surgery",
