  "answer": "C) In ZES gastrin levels may be only mildly elevated but can be increased with provoca-tion with intravenous calcium or secretin. Most patients with gastrinoma have serum gastrin levels that exceed 500 pg/mL. When the range is lower than 200–500 pg/mL, a stimulation test is performed to confirm the diagnosis. A rise of 200 pg/mL after 15 minutes, or a dou-bling of the fasting level is diagnostic. ZES can occur sporadically or as part of multiple endocrine neoplasia (MEN) I.",
