  "question": "A 62-year-old man presents with guaiac posi-tive stool. He is asymptomatic. Workup reveals a 2-cm ulcerated carcinoma on the antral lesser curvature. Tumor markers are negative. ACAT scan is negative for metastatic disease and lym-phadenopathy liver function tests are normal. What is the correct treatment for this patient?",
