  "question": "A63-year-old woman is admitted to the hospi-tal with a UGI bleed that subsides sponta-neously within a short time after admission. A barium study shows a gastric ulceration that is described by the radiologist as having a “dough-nut sign.” What is the most likely diagnosis?",
