  "question": "A 45-year-old pilot has retrosternal burning, especially when he eats and lies down to go to sleep. He has self-medicated himself with over the counter heartburn medications. Upper endoscopy reveals an erythematous and inflammed distal esophagus. In severe reflux esophagitis, the resting pressure of the LES is decreased. This may be physiologically increased by which of the following?",
