  "question": "A 40-year-old woman complains of heartburn located in the epigastic and retrosternal areas. She also has symptoms of regurgitation. Endoscopy shows erythema of the esophagus consistent with reflux esophagitis. The patient has tried conservative measures, including PPls with no improvement in symptoms. Which of the following is TRUE?",
