  "answer": "E) Endoscopic findings range from petechiae to multiple ulcers in the body of the stomach and duodenum. Endoscopy can safely be performed at the bedside in the intensive care unit. Because bleeding may be secondary to shallow mucosal erosions, a CAT scan, UGI series, and angiogram will not be diagnostic. Capsule endoscopy is sometimes used in the diagnosis of occult gas-trointestinal bleeding when other methods have not been helpful.",
