  "question": "A 33-year-old man is admitted to the hospital for evaluation and treatment of a gastrojejunal ulcer. At age 25, he was treated surgically with an omental (Graham) patch for a perforated duodenal ulcer. At age 30, he was treated with a truncal vagotomy and antrectomy for a chronic duodenal ulcer. He now has a stomal (gastrojejunal) ulcer that is refractory to med-ical therapy. Which of the following should be checked?",
