  "answer": "C) There are multiple morbid obesity opera-tions. Jejunoileal bypass has a higher incidence of both early and late complications. Gastric restrictive procedures (e.g., vertical banded gastroplasty) are generally less effective than GBP. GBPpatients can be expected to lose up to two-thirds of their weight initially. The gastric pouch capacity should be no larger than 30cc. Anastomotic leak rate should be less than 5%.",
