  "answer": "C) It is important to rule out coronary artery disease in patients who have DES because the symptoms may be similar. Barium swallow and endoscopy are used to evaluate the esophagus. Acorkscrew esophagus is highly suggestive of DES, however, it is not always seen. Manometry is the diagnostic study of choice. Medical management includes nitrates and calcium channel blockers.",
