  "question": "A 54-year-old man presents with a massive UGI bleed. After resuscitation, endoscopy is performed. No esophageal varices, gastritis, or gastric ulcers are seen. After copious irrigation, a pinpoint lesion is seen near the GE junction. What can be said about this lesion?",
