  "answer": "E) Adieulafoy lesion is an uncommon cause of UGI bleeding (0.3–7%). It can occur anywhere in the gastrointestinal tract, but is most commonly found in the stomach (near the GE junction). It is often difficult to visualize because of its small size. Adilated submucosal artery is the source of the bleeding. First-line management is therapeutic endoscopy. There is no association with NSAIDs or alcohol. These lesions are more common in men.",
