  "question": "A55-year-old man presents with left lower quad-rant (LLQ) abdominal pain of 2-day duration, associated with constipation. On physical exam-ination, he has tenderness localized to the LLQ with fullness in that area leukocyte count is 22,000 and temperature is 101.5°F. Which would be the best diagnostic study to evaluate this man?",
