  "question": "A 42-year-old woman is admitted to the emergency department with severe colicky pain, vomiting, and abdominal distention. She has not passed stools or flatus for 48 hours. X-rays of the abdomen confirm the presence of small-bowel obstruction. What is the most likely cause of small-bowel obstruction in this patient?",
