  "answer": "C) The ileum is the exclusive site of bile salt absorption, and failure of its absorption contributes to the steatorrhea. Ileal resection, which at times includes the ileocecal valve, is more commonly performed than is proximal resection. Over a longer period of time (2–3 years), megaloblastic anemia occurs.",
  "chapter": "General Surgery",
