  "answer": "A) In the blind loop syndrome, bacteria proliferate in an affected segment that fails to show appropriate peristaltic activity. It may be seen in surgery requiring jejunal or ileal bypass, small intestinal diverticular disease, scleroderma, diabetes mellitus, and intestinal carcinoma. Macrocytic anemia, caused by malabsorption of Vitamin B and folic acid, is a key diagnostic feature in its diagnosis.",
  "chapter": "General Surgery",
