  "answer": "C) Both zinc and vitamin C (ascarbate) deficiency, impair wound healing. Vitamin A deficiency is also implicated in would healing and supplemental Vitamin A has been shown in experimental studies to prevent radiation included defects in wound healing. Incision through the same abdominal wall scar incision actually promotes wound healing, because the initial lag interval after creation of the wound is avoided (unless the whole scar of the incision is removed). Increase in local oxygen tension actually promotes wound healing.",
