  "question": "A 12-year-old boy complains of pain in the lower abdomen (mainly on the right side). Symptoms commenced 12 hours before admission. He had noted anorexia during this period. Examination revealed tenderness in the right iliac fossa, which was maximal 1 cm below Mc Burney’s point. In appendicitis, where does the pain frequently commence?",
