  "id": 130456,
  "question": "A28-old-male from Kosovo, who lives alone, presents with diarrhea. On examination he manifests clear wasting and malnutrition. His hematocrit (HCT) is 28%, serum albumin reduced to 2.8 g%, and the blood analysis shows a macrocytic anemia. The emergency department physician is unable to secure an accurate history of the nature of multiple previous operations he had undergone before his arrival in the United States several months previously. What is the likely diagnosis that explains these features?",
