  "answer": "C) Irradiation of the abdominal cavity of more than 50 Gy is associated with a higher rate of complications. The incidence of symptomatic sigmoiditis may be as high as 75%, and histologically abnormal rectal biopsy findings occur in 11% of patients undergoing treatment for pelvic malignancy. Previous surgery with possible adhesion formation increases the risk of irradiation damage.",
  "chapter": "General Surgery",
