  "answer": "A) Mechanical obstruction implies a barrier that impedes progress of intestinal contents. Complete mid- or distal small-bowel obstruction presents with colicky abdominal pain, more marked abdominal distention but with vomiting that is less frequent and occurs at a later stage than that of proximal jejunal obstruction.",
