  "answer": "E) MMC are isoperistaltic waves and occur approximately once every 90 minutes. Oral feeding inhibits the MMC for as much as 3–4 hours. The inhibition of the MMC in the stomach and intestine may account in part for nausea and vomiting occurring after surgery. The major force that drives chyme aborally is that of segmentation and not the MMC.",
