  "question": "A 45-year-old man with hepatitis C undergoes an uneventful percutaneous liver biopsy. About 6-weeks later, he complains of RUQ pain, is clinically jaundiced, with a hemoglobin of 9.2 mg/dLand is fecal occult blood positive. Which diagnosis best explains this patient’s symptoms?",
