  "question": "A40-year-old woman with severe chronic pan-creatitis is scheduled to undergo an operation, because other forms of treatment have failed. The ultrasound shows no evidence of pseudo-cyst formation or cholelithiasis and endoscopic retrograde cholangiopancreatogram (ERCP) demonstrates dilated pancreatic ducts with multiple stricture formation. Which operation is suitable to treat this condition?",
