  "question": "A 30-year-old male is admitted with frequent episodes of hypoglycemia. Biochemical investi-gations confirmed an insulinoma. Localization studies were carried out. ACT scan and magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) of the abdomen failed to reveal a tumor in the pancreas. An endoscopic ultrasound, however, localized a 2-cm insuli-noma in the tail of the pancreas. What should be the next step in the management of this patient?",
