  "answer": "C) Patients with biliary dyskinesia present with typical symptoms of gallstone disease, but investigations fail to reveal cholelithiasis or choledocholithiasis. Ironically, many patients will have undergone cholecystectomy for inci-dentally found gallstones but without relief of pain. ERCP with measurement of sphincter pressure will reveal basal sphincter pressure above 40 cm of water. Calcium channel block-ers may be tried initially to relieve the spasm of the sphincter of Oddi, but many patients will require an endoscopic sphincterotomy.",
  "chapter": "General Surgery",
