  "answer": "B) Sclerosing cholangitis is rare and occurs mainly in the third and fourth decades of life. Unlike most autoimmune disorders, it affects men more commonly. It may occur without any other abnormal pathology or may be asso-ciated with ulcerative colitis or retroperitoneal fibrosis. The CBD is converted to a thickened cord whose lumen is almost completely oblit-erated. The prognosis is guarded, and the mean survival is only 5–6 years.",
  "chapter": "General Surgery",
