  "answer": "A) Radioactive technetium (99mTc) scan to see if a retained accessory spleen (splenunculus) is present, which may account for postoperative thrombocytopenia. Radioactive technetium (not I135) is used to localize splenic tissue. Patients with ITP have petechiae, ecchymosis, and/or bleeding. Splenectomy performed ini-tially for ITPis likely to be successful in 80% of patients, but is less effective in older patients.",
