  "answer": "E) In Richter’s hernia, part of the bowel wall is entrapped in the hernia sac. This results in a par-tial occlusion of the lumen and bowel movement remains possible, despite strangulation and gan-grene of the entrapped portion. Evaluation at surgery, of the viability of the full-bowel wall must always be carried out before returning the entrapped segment to the peritoneal cavity.",
