  "question": "A 70-year-old, moderately obese, male pres-ents with a large, midline incisional hernia. One year previously, he underwent a colon resection for adenocarcinoma. Colonoscopy, metastasis workup and carcinoembryonic anti-gen (CEA) are normal. Which of the following statement is TRUE?",
