  "question": "A62-year-old postal officer develops minimal urinary symptoms. His PSA level is elevated and continues to increase during a 6-month period of observation. The next step in evaluation, if transrectal ultrasound (TRUS) prostate biopsy (Fig. 9–1) were positive for adenocarcinoma of prostate, would be:",
