  "answer": "A) Ceftizoxime (Cefizox) is not effective against many strains of Pseudomonas. If the drug is used, a higher dosage may be indicated, and the antibiotic should be changed if a quick response does not occur. Complications may occur in patients who are allergic to penicillin.",
