  "question": "A 24-year-old bank clerk is admitted to the hospital with left-sided blindness. She had emigrated from Africa and had been treated for sickle-cell disease. Examination reveals bleeding into the posterior (vitreous) chamber of the eye. Funduscopy cannot be done because of the presence of blood inside the eye. What should be the next step in management?",
