  "question": "A 62-year-old woman underwent a modified mastectomy operation 5 years ago. One month before hospital admission, she undergoes repeated paracentesis of her left pleural cavity for a malignant effusion. The effusion recurred, as seen on x-ray, and she complains of dyspnea. What would appropriate therapy include?",
