  "question": "A34-year-old woman with Crohn’s disease has undergone her fifth operation with small-bowel resection. She has hemoglobin of 7 g/dL. An upper gastrointestinal (GI) series shows an apple-core lesion due to adenocarcinoma of the small bowel (Fig. 14–1). What is the most likely cause of her anemia?",
