  "answer": "B) Cystic astrocytomas are neoplasms of the CNS. They usually consist of a large, nonen-hancing cyst on the wall of which is an enhanc-ing tumor nodule. They are most commonly found within the substance of the cerebellar hemispheres of children and young adults. A Rathke’s cleft cyst is a remnant of the embry-ologic Rathke’s pouch. These are found within the sella turcica.",
