  "answer": "D) In addition to necrosis of the superficial and deep fascia, thrombosis of the microcirculation of the subcutaneous tissue occurs. Mortality rates have been reduced from 80% in the past to less than 12% in recent series. Polymicrobial infection is more commonly encountered, and gram-positive and gram-negative organisms are found in 70% of cases. Treatment is based on adequate debridement and use of appropriate broad-spectrum antibiotics.",
