  "question": "A 7-week-old girl is referred by her pediatrician for projectile vomiting over the past week. Her weight has remained stable, her fontanelles are not sunken and she sucks avidly. Her abdomen is soft with visible peristalsis in the epigastrium without evidence of a mass. A diagnosis of pyloric stenosis, in this case (Fig. 13–1)",
