  "answer": "D) Children’s kidneys do not acquire significant ability to concentrate sodium until well after the age of 2 years. D5 / NS is the most appropriate maintenance fluid for young children with normal electrolytes. The baseline fluid requirement for children is 100 mL/kgd for the first 10 kg, 50 mL/kgd for the second 10 kg, and 25 mL/kgd for each kg thereafter. (nb: Premature infants will require significantly more.) This child’s requirement can be calculated as follows: 10 kg × 100 mL/kgd + 1 kg × 10 mL/kgd = 1050 mL/d = 44 mL/h.",
