  "question": "A 15 kg, 7-year-old girl is in the emergency room with dramatic blood loss from a scalp laceration after blunt trauma. Suturing the laceration has achieved hemostasis but she is lethargic and clammy with digital and perioral cyanosis. Her heart rate is 110 bpm and blood pressure is 80/40 mm Hg. The most appropriate initial fluid order is",
