  "question": "A 60-year-old man is brought into the emergency department after being hit by a car. His blood pressure is 70 mm Hg palpable, and abdomen is massively distended and tender. A large, stellate fracture of the right lower liver is noted, and despite repeated attempts at suturing, bleeding persists. The anesthesiologist notes that the pH of arterial blood is 7.2 and that the patient has become hypothermic. A total of 8 U of blood have been transfused. What is the next step in management?",
