  "id": 130835,
  "question": "A7-year-old boy falls off his bicycle, landing on the left elbow. He presents to the emergency room with massive, tense swelling of the elbow with painful and restricted elbow motion. X-rays show a displaced fracture of the distal end of the humerus. Which of the following is the most serious complication of this fracture?",
  "options": {
    "A": "Nonunion of fracture fragments",
    "B": "Nonunion of fracture fragments with deformity",
    "C": "Disruption of the growth plate at the distal end of the humerus",
    "D": "Forearm compartment syndrome (Volkmann’s ischemia)",
    "E": "Ankylosis of the elbow joint"
  },
